  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nCurrently, if both users have enabled \"Mutual contact request\" (that should be enabled by default in https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/issues/14541) after User1 deletes User2 from contact list, 1-1 chat is empty for both users\r\n\r\nThe design is here: https://www.figma.com/file/PiN0uwRgZj4L9U4N7xO7Xb/Profile-for-Mobile?node-id=3480%3A296202&t=0e4zQn11YmuFJFqv-4 , but until it is done for dogfooding it should be enough to make some explanation how to make it work again (i. e. placeholder, ugly one just to avoid misleading with actual implementation)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\ncan see chat history, cannot send messages with some explanation, i.e.\r\n![Monosnap 2022-12-22 18-38-37](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/209194170-bf55cfa7-d012-4bd8-81b1-7b9e6d7a957c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nChat history and message sending are blocked for both User1 and User2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4557972/209194417-bb3ed636-898b-4f17-986d-d1d95b39b390.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) User1 and User2 enable \"Mutual contacts\" in Profile > Settings > Advanced\r\n2) User1 adds User2 to contacts\r\n3) User2 accepts the contact request\r\n4) User1 and User2 exchange several messages in chat\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 22/12/22\r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
